@Node "What is IR-Master" "ir-master26e.guide/What is IR-Master"
@Next "Installation"
@Prev "Main"
@Toc "Main"

What is IR-Master
*****************

   The IR-Master project consists of two software components and a
control hardware, which is connected to the joystick port of your Amiga.

   At first you start edition your @{i}virtual@{ui} remote control with the
IR-Editor, See @{"IR-Editor" Link "IR-Editor"}. This one is saved to disk then. And you
activate the IR-Runner, See @{"IR-Runner" Link "IR-Runner"}.

   Your edited remote control opens as a window on the workbench. With
this window you can interactively control your device[s], you can use
the IR-Runner's @{i}ARexx-port@{ui} for programming your devices, See @{"ARexx Port" Link "ARexx Port"}.
Finally you can send infra red codes from within other applications or
edit scripts which will automatically control e.g. your video recorder.

   Since version 2.5 of the IR-Master two new features were introduced:
You can directly send commands to @{i}LControl@{ui} and @{i}Rapid@{ui}. This allows you
to control video cameras supported with an @{i}LANC/Control-L@{ui}interface and
video recorders supported with an @{i}GSE-Rapid-interface@{ui}. For more
information, please consult @{"LControl & Rapid" Link "LControl & Rapid"}.


@EndNode

@Node "Installation" "ir-master26e.guide/Installation"
@Next "IR-Editor"
@Prev "What is IR-Master"
@Toc "Main"

Installation
************

   Requirements:

@{i}req.library@{ui}
     may not be includet in this package, but can be easily found -
     it's freely distribatable and written by Colin Fox (Pyramid
     Designs) and Bruce Dawson (Cygnus Software), See @{"req.library" Link "req.library"}.

@{i}Kick/WB 1.x@{ui}
     for the poor and old (but working!) version look at @{b}Readme13@{ub}

@{i}Kick/WB 2.x/3.x@{ui}
     for the fine and new (also working :-)version.

   Installation:

  1. Copy the @{b}req.library@{ub} to your @{b}LIBS:@{ub} drawer of your boot disk.

     A patch (like @{i}RTPatch@{ui} from Nico Francois) is recommended to patch
     the @{i}req.library@{ui} calls to the much better looking @{i}reqtools.library@{ui}
     (also from Nico Francois ->thanks). See @{"Other Software" Link "Other Software"}.

  2. Create a directory for the IR-Editor and the IR-Runner and copy
     them to this directory. However, it is not needed for the two
     programs to be in a certain drawer. No assigns are needed.

     @{i}Note:@{ui}

     Your IR-Runner should be placed in a directory that is in the
     workbench search path (which is declared in your @{b}startup-sequence@{ub}
     right before @{b}loadwb@{ub}), e.g. @{b}C:@{ub} or @{b}sys:utilities@{ub}.  So the projects
     will surely find the default tool.

  3.     If you use WB 2.1 or higher:

     Copy the languages-catalog you want to use from @{b}catalogs/<language>@{ub}
     to
     @{b}LOCALE:catalogs/<language>@{ub}. At the moment there is only german and
     english (built-in).


@EndNode

