IR-Runner Menus
===============

   Each remote control has its own gui and its own menu:

@{i}About@{ui}
     Gives you VERY important information about you, god and the
     universe.

@{i}Hide@{ui}
     Closes the gui. The @{i}arexx port@{ui} will still be available.

@{i}Fix Position@{ui}
     Saves the current IR-Runner window position to the project's icon
     (as tooltypes).

@{i}Quit@{ui}
     Quits this remote control.


@EndNode

@Node "ARexx Port" "ir-master26e.guide/ARexx Port"
@Next "Tooltypes"
@Prev "IR-Runner Menus"
@Toc "IR-Runner"

ARexx Port
==========

   The IR-Runner has it's own rexx port. The port name depends on the
project's name:

     Project name: @{i}CD_Player.irm@{ui} ==> port name: @{i}CD_Player_rexx@{ui}

   Now the commands:

@{i}IR_Send@{ui}
     The IR_Send command needs one parameter:
        @{b}*@{ub} Either the gadget number (the number shown in the editor when
          the gadget is selected)

        @{b}*@{ub} or: the gadget's text (if it is no grafic!) Therefore you must
          specify a @{b}$@{ub} followed by the gadget text.       From the shell
     this could look like this:

          1> rx "address 'CD_Player_rexx' IR_Send 3"
     or in a rexx script:

          /* cd player -> play */
          
          address 'CD_Player_rexx'
          IR_Send '$Play'     /* assuming that the gadget's text is 'Play' */
          
          exit

@{i}IR_Move@{ui}
     With the IR_Move command you can move the window (if opened). This
     command needs two arguments, the x and y coordinate of the new
     window position.

     Example:
          IR_Move 100 120

@{i}IR_Quit@{ui}
     Quits the application.

@{i}IR_Disappear@{ui}
     Closes the gui without closing the rexx port. It acts like
     selecting hide from the menu/clicking hide in commodities
     exchange. No arguments are needed.

@{i}IR_Appear@{ui}
     Opens the gui (if cosed) and (if cosed) reopens the rexx port. No
     args.

@{i}IR_Disable@{ui}
     Acts like IR_Disappear but the rexx port is closed, too. More
     memory is freed again.  No args.

@{i}IR_Enable@{ui}
     Reopens (if closed) the rexx port and reopens (if closed) the gui.
     No args.


@EndNode

@Node "Tooltypes" "ir-master26e.guide/Tooltypes"
@Prev "ARexx Port"
@Toc "IR-Runner"

Tooltypes
=========

   The IR-Runner recognizes the following tooltypes, when given in the
project icon:

@{i}CX_POPKEY="string"@{ui}
     Here you can specify a hotkey - with this shortcut, you can
     activate this IR-Runner project

     Example: @{i}CX_POPKEY=lalt f10@{ui} If you hold @{b}left-alt@{ub} and press @{b}f10@{ub},
     this IR-Runner project wil be activatet.

@{i}CX_POPUP=YES|NO@{ui}
     If you specify @{b}NO@{ub}, no window will be opened when starting this
     project. You can control this project only via ARexx and
     Commodities-Exchange. However you can open the project's window by
     ARexx/Cx.

@{i}LEFT=xxx@{ui}
     Here you can specify the default left coordinate of the window.
     This tooltype is automatically generated when selecting @{i}fix
     position@{ui} in the menu.

@{i}TOP=yyy@{ui}
     The default top coordinate of the window.

@{i}BACKGROUND=name@{ui}
     Here the background grafik is specified.

@{i}PUBSCREEN=name@{ui}
     name is the title of a public screen on which the IR-Runner should
     open its gui.


@EndNode

@Node "Hardwaretuning" "ir-master26e.guide/Hardwaretuning"
@Next "Appendix"
@Prev "IR-Runner"
@Toc "Main"

Hardwaretuning
**************

   The normal range of the IR-Master is ca. 1-2 m. In the most cases
this is enough. For those people who need more:

   @{b}*@{ub} exchange R2 with 150 Ohm ==> ca 3 m

   @{b}*@{ub} exchange R2 with 100-120 Ohm ==> ca 4 m  *)

   @{b}*@{ub} 2 * D1 in row, R2:100 Ohm ==> ca 5 m

   @{b}*@{ub} 2 * D1 in row, R2:82 Ohm ==> ca 6 m  *)

   @{b}*@{ub} exchange D1 with LDR 273 or SFH 485 (e.g. Konrad Elec.) and R2 :
     75 - 100 Ohm ==> up to 10 m

   @{i}Important@{ui}

   The configurations which are marked with a '*' must only be plugged
in when the port is initialized, that means when IR-Editor/IR-Runner is
already started. IF NOT, THE IR-SENDER WILL BE DAMAGED AFTER A WHILE.

   Now have fun.....


@EndNode

